In the bare 2D film, as the temperature decreases from 295 K to 100 K, the X emission lifetime decreases and the DX emission emerges with an increasingly long lifetime and increasingly strong intensity, as has previously been observed by Fang et al. (Fig. 4b, dark teal trace, 100 K)38. Further reductions in temperature show that, as the back transfer ks−(T)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
